ddf.catalog.endpoint

Interface CatalogEndpoint

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CatalogEndpointImpl

    public interface CatalogEndpoint
    CatalogEndpoint represents an endpoint that accesses the catalog and wants to advertise itself to the system. It does this by providing a map of properties about itself. An example use of this interface is the registry framework which uses the interface to identify which endpoints can be used as federation methods.
